description:
"We acknowledge our error in not stating that data from TraceTogether is not exempt from the Criminal Procedure Code. I take full responsibility for this mistake."

In a Parliament session on Feb. 2, Minister Vivian Balakrishnan addressed privacy concerns over the TraceTogether programme, adding that he "regret[s] the consternation [and] the anxiety" caused.

He further emphasised that TraceTogether and other digital contact tracing programmes would be deactivated when Covid-19 is over.

comments: Singapore‚Äôs governing system is much to be commended. Some Singaporeans don‚Äôt know how lucky they are... I moved back to Singapore from Europe and I can safely say Europe‚Äôs way of handling the Covid-19 pandemic is pre-historic compared to Singapore‚Äôs. Another factor is that Singaporeans are compliant and adhere to the law passed down by the govt, while Europe‚Äôs people are in a mess, and their left and right wings are tearing apart further amidst the pandemic. After being back here, I never felt more lucky and grateful to be Singaporean.

description:
Responding to a parliamentary question on Feb. 1, Minister for Education Lawrence Wong warned that issues of gender identity have become "bitterly contested sources of division in the culture wars in some Western countries and societies".

He added, "We should not import these culture wars into Singapore, or allow issues of gender identity to divide our society."

Schools can exercise flexibility if there are valid medical grounds and work out practical arrangements for transgender students who may face difficulty with certain rules.

comments: maybe if you were inclusive to those students and accommodated to their needs while also educating cis people about it then maybe we wouldn't have this kind of discourse in the first place??

Schools can exercise flexibility if there are valid medical grounds and work out practical arrangements for transgender students who may face difficulty with certain rules.

comments: Transgenderedness is not a disease. Gender disphoria my ass! Focusing this discourse on medical conditions and placing this issue with medical professionals senda a clear message that trans people are SICK, which they are not. It only creates more stigma, prejudice and divisiveness. Schools are the first socialization point for children and its role is not only provide information to be retained as knowledge, but also allow students to develop social skills to function in collective society when they become adults. So yes, matters of inclusiveness, compassion, acceptance and coliving with differences IS a school matter and should be reflected in both policy and syllabus. Anything less than that is overt public neglect for the social group which is being disregarded, in this case trans people.

description:
"Once Covid-19 pandemic is over, and there is no longer a need for contact tracing, we will most happily and cheerfully stand the [TraceTogether] programme down."

At a Parliament session on Jan. 5 2021, Minister Vivian Balakrishnan addressed questions on privacy concerns regarding the use of TraceTogether in criminal investigations. He added that he had not thought of the application of the Criminal Procedure Code (CPC) to TraceTogether data in an earlier statement about the matter.

description:
In response to NCMP Leong Mun Wai's question on how Singapore can reopen its borders to foreigners, Minister Lawrence Wong said that every time a measure is relaxed, there is increased risk and "all of the risks do add up".

He added that one factor which would let Singapore open up more would be vaccinations, but expects that a "significant number of people" would be vaccinated only by the third quarter of the year.

He added that one factor which would let Singapore open up more would be vaccinations, but expects that a "significant number of people" would be vaccinated only by the third quarter of the year.

comments: Lawrence Wong has lost some hair

description:
The token is available for free for all residents in Singapore, and every resident in Singapore is encouraged to either download the TraceTogether app or to collect a TraceTogether Token. These updates were announced by Minister-in-charge of the Smart Nation Initiative Vivian Balakrishnan in a virtual press conference by the the Multi-Ministry Taskforce (MTF) on Wednesday (Sep. 9).

This round of distribution will begin in the Jalan Besar and Tanjong Pagar regions, where there is a higher concentration of elderly individuals, and the nextended throughout Singapore progressively.

description:
Speaking to the press on Sept. 9, Minister Lawrence Wong said that to date, there are still people flouting safe distancing measures, especially when they dine out.

"I would say our ability to continue on this path of progressive resumption of activities rests largely on two factors‚Äî one, we have to control the infection and keep numbers down... But secondly, it also depends on our ability to comply with existing measures."

"It's also not fair for the majority of operators who are complying with the rules, and yet these few are taking their chances and breaching the rules. So our enforcement agencies will be stepping up spot checks, as well as enforcement actions."

"I would say our ability to continue on this path of progressive resumption of activities rests largely on two factors‚Äî one, we have to control the infection and keep numbers down... But secondly, it also depends on our ability to comply with existing measures."

"It's also not fair for the majority of operators who are complying with the rules, and yet these few are taking their chances and breaching the rules. So our enforcement agencies will be stepping up spot checks, as well as enforcement actions."

description:
Did you know that elephants are keystone species? Keystone species are species whose survival is critical to the survival of others in the ecosystem. In this case, elephant poop has a pretty important role in it.

Have an up-close and personal experience with these majestic beasts from the comfort of your own home.

Note: Some footage in the video shows an earlier elephant presentation format that has been revamped by Singapore Zoo from 2018. According to Singapore Zoo, this is done in line with animal welfare guidelines and best practices for safety, where animals and keepers are not placed in a shared space. Activities which the elephants are involved in now are voluntary and enrichment-based.

comments: In zoos, animals are there for the entertainment of humans. Even when that entertainment has a degree of education, animals are still captive for our benefit. We can learn about animals and wildlife in many ways, we don‚Äôt have to keep them in zoos for the sake of our own education.Even in zoos where conservation is a priority, there is still the issue that the freedoms and needs of individual animals are compromised in the name of ‚Äòthe greater good‚Äô. It is still speciesist to assume that we have the right to keep animals captive, even if we believe the ultimate outcomes associated with preventing extinction are positive.Animals are not able to thrive in such small places. Even ‚Äògood‚Äô zoos simply can‚Äôt afford to provide spaces large enough to satisfy the normal roaming and exploring instincts of many animals. And as for bad zoos, some of the conditions can be so cramped and awful that animals suffer from ‚Äòzoochosis‚Äô ‚Äì if you see an animal rocking back and forth, it‚Äôs likely that it‚Äôs suffering severe mental depression from being copped up in such confined and inadequate conditions.Even if enclosures are of an adequate size, most zoos provide a chance to see non-native animals from completely different parts of the world. This can mean that animals are often kept in climates very different from the ones they should be living in. Even if the animals receive a good standard of care, it can‚Äôt be good to keep them in an alien environment.If people want to see animals and fund something positive, there are plenty of amazing animal sanctuaries that desperately need money for upkeep, rescue operations, education programs, and investigations. Most zoos are for-profit operations, whereas animal sanctuaries prioritise the safety, comfort, and wellbeing of the animals.

Note: Some footage in the video shows an earlier elephant presentation format that has been revamped by Singapore Zoo from 2018. According to Singapore Zoo, this is done in line with animal welfare guidelines and best practices for safety, where animals and keepers are not placed in a shared space. Activities which the elephants are involved in now are voluntary and enrichment-based.

description:
"So I think let's not jump to the conclusion just because we see queues forming, queues form everywhere and not just when people go and cast the vote, queues form in FNB outlets, queues form in hawker centers and markets, so there are queues everywhere."

At a press conference on July 17, Minister Lawrence Wong addressed the possibility of new clusters happening after GE2020. He pointed out the safety procedures ELD has taken and mentioned that queueing does not necessarily "cause the transmission of the virus". He also emphasised the need for individuals to take "responsibility for our own behaviors".

description:
"Frankly a lot of diplomacy is conducted through WhatsApp and other messaging platforms. It's informal, our staff get very nervous that we might say things or give away things. It lends a sense of immediacy and intimacy which you will not get just with formal letters or even at formal meetings."

20/20/20 is a video series where we have politicians answer 20 questions by 20 people in their 20s.

We got Vivian Balakrishnan, Minister for Foreign Affairs, to answer questions from youths on what regional neighbours will be watching for as they observe our GE, the possibility of voting online and how he ended up taking that selfie with Kim Jong Un.

description:
Now you can remember what the sea and sweaty strangers smell like.

Starting Friday, Jun.19, many public facilities will be open again, such as swimming complexes, playgrounds and sports halls. Also reopening are aesthetic services such as beauty salons, gyms and private enrichment classes. However, there will be some restrictions regarding social distancing -- for example, at any one time, even while exiting the premises, there must not be more than a group of 5 people.

comments: I really love all the songs!!! Some of them really open me up to new genres of modern day music (pop). The album has also opened me up to many new songs to binge-listen to when im in the mood to grove a little to some music. I really enjoyed the album and all the different themes, the styles that she experimented with like some bits and pieces of like ‚Äò80s or ‚Äò90s vibes in the songs. Im really looking forward to more music from her!!

comments: 'Cool' 's the best, its got that breezy vibe - that synth riff that starts from the beginning of the song which carries to the end, oh man, it makes you feel like youre having a carefree summer day, and you can forget about everything that's been happening so far. Dua's vocals are exceptionally strong and prominent throughout the song and so is not overshadowed by the electronic sound. It manages to sound like a modern pop song and yet also bring out the nostalgic 2000s dance-pop song sound at the same time, I can hear 'cool' drawing inspiration from that era like from Gwen Stefani for example, and these influences adds the cherry on top of this already splendid song!

comments: Every. Single. Song in this album is so amazing, it was almost tough to find a favourite. All the songs are BOPS. However, one of my favourite songs off the album has to be love again. It's catchy tunes, lyric structure, the meaning behind the lyrics and Dua's strong, prominent and amazing vocals make it one of the best songs of her album. Most importantly, the star-wars like feel to the song just makes me want to get up and dance. Love again has a certain uniqueness to it that just makes the song so special. So so thankful of her to release such a catchy, fun and entertaining album during this tough period. Every time I listen to it, I just take my mind off things, relax, and have a little fun once in a while. Best album of 2020!!! I love @dualipa so much!!!!!!!

The total number of cases in Japan is close to 10,000, prompting Japan's Prime Minister Shinzo Abe to declare a nationwide state of emergency. Meanwhile, Taiwan reported no new cases for the second time this week.

On April 16, Singapore reported 728 new cases of Covid-19, another record-high increase. The total number of cases in Singapore has now surpassed 4,000. Look at the top few countries, they have very widespread population but still is transmitting at a faster rate than we are(some while under lockdown). description:
On keeping schools open, PM Lee said today (Mar. 27) that closing schools does not solve any problems. 
He also stated that if teachers are unable to socialise and guide children, and if parents are unable to make for the lack of enrichment at home, children will be put at a disadvantage.

comments: The government can't have full control over every school. There are schools such as mine where ants can be commonly found dead in food and where measurements are so incredibly lax to the point where we once kept our thermometers together in a box. Not the kind u put in ur ear, the kind where one would have to suck on. Not only that, we aren't allowed to go to washrooms to wash them, nor ask others for tissues. So most people just wipe it off their shirt with some just shoving it back in. The government is mostly just dedicating resources and care to high end schools such as HCI, RGS, RVHS, and completely ignoring some low end schools such as mine for instance. Honestly, there is no way to truly confirm that all schools are taking appropriate measures to protect students from this disease or any other sort of disaster. Plus, Secondary school students tend to leave home regardless, so does that not make it any different from letting them stay at home? Besides, nowadays, parents being wary and worried over their child's well being, they'd probably force their child to stay at home. But for school, not everyone can fetch their children home can they?

On keeping schools open, PM Lee said today (Mar. 27) that closing schools does not solve any problems. 
He also stated that if teachers are unable to socialise and guide children, and if parents are unable to make for the lack of enrichment at home, children will be put at a disadvantage.

Apart from entertainment venues, all centre-based tuition and enrichment classes will be suspended to reduce the intermingling of students from different schools.

Organised tours in public venues (such as sightseeing or guided walking tours) will also be suspended.

Photo from Zouk SG

comments: Frightening fact on COVID 19 infection:Make no mistake. When loved ones are removed from your home by ambulance because the virus has hit them hard, you are not going to be able to follow them there, sit by their hospital bed and hold their hand. You are not going to be able to pop in at 7.00 pm for visiting hours. They are going to have no one other than exhausted and brave hospital staff to see them through days or weeks of barely breathing through a ventilator until they either die or recover. They are not going to be well enough to text you.You are not going to be able to phone the ward to check in on them regularly (staff will be too busy for that). During that time, they will be completely alone, while you sit at home waiting to hear whether they have made it through.Imagine that person is someone you love dearly. Because it's going to be a reality for many in the coming weeks.And if that person in hospital happens to be you, going through that ordeal completely alone, it would be nothing less than terrifying.Please stay home and only go out if absolutely necessary. Social distancing is imperative right now for your family and mine.Copy and paste to share, I did.

description:
Called TraceTogether, the mobile app enables community-driven contact tracing through short-distance Bluetooth signals between mobile phones that have the app installed.

The app estimates the distance between users, as well as the duration of their encounters to identify those who were in close contact with a confirmed Covid-19 case.

The records of these encounters are encrypted and stored locally on each user‚Äôs phone for 21 days, which covers the incubation period of the coronavirus.

Photo by Syahindah Ishak

The app estimates the distance between users, as well as the duration of their encounters to identify those who were in close contact with a confirmed Covid-19 case.

The records of these encounters are encrypted and stored locally on each user‚Äôs phone for 21 days, which covers the incubation period of the coronavirus.

Photo by Syahindah Ishak

description:
This helps with contact tracing, but why is tracing recovered patients important?

The problem with contact tracing is that the trail can be lost when one is unable to make connections to previous cases.

This could happen if the tests are unable to detect the presence of Covid-19 in a spreader who has recovered. .

If Singapore is not able to determine the source, infections and clusters would be harder to contain.

description:
Despite effective contact tracing, it was previously unknown how the Grace Assembly of God (GAOG) churches came to become the largest cluster of Covid-19 cases in Singapore.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
CID's investigations reveal that the virus likely originated with Case 8 and 9. They are Chinese nationals from Wuhan who had also been to Life Church and Missions on Jan. 19.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
They infected six other people at the church, two of which headed for a Chinese New year gathering at Mei Hwan Drive on Jan. 25.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
Seven more people, including a staff member with GAOG, were subsequently infected after this gathering.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
Image from GAOG.
